    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-03-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-03-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="303"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d303">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.001G29/15.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">British Ambassador</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-03-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 18, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 1111.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: Referring to your No. 28 of the 17th
                    ultimo, extending an invitation from your Government to the Government of the
                    United States to have a man-of-war present at the naval review to be held at
                    Spithead on Saturday the 24th of June on the occasion of <pb facs="0335" n="253"
                        xml:id="pg_253"/> the coronation of His Britannic Majesty, George V, I take
                    pleasure in informing you of the receipt of a letter from the Secretary of the
                    Navy, dated March 9, 1911,<note n="1" xml:id="d303fn1">Not printed.</note> in
                    which he states that the U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Delaware</hi> has been
                    designated to represent this Government on that occasion.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
